<td valign="top" class="postbody">
<hr />
I'm about to start working as a buyers' agent for a Real Estate Company here in Columbus in addition to my real estate marketing/support business. I've been training for what seems like forever. I used to think it was a waste of time to use a buyers' agent until I went through all of the training and realized the expertise they can bring to the table for FREE. It's actually a huge benefit and costs you nothing as long as the listing agent or builder is willing to do a co-op (pay their commission). Buying a house is a huge investment so use a buyers' agent, especially if it's your first house. Almost every real estate company has them now. They'll guide you through each step of the process to make sure you aren't being taken advantage of. They work for you not the seller, unlike the listing agent who works for the seller. With that being said it's still very important for you to do your homework with financing and budgeting.
<br />

<br />
Also, from what I've heard from other real estate professionals this whole lawsuit is the result of a feud between two wealthy families one of which builds homes and the other who prints news. If you look into it the whole thing really makes no sense, in that all the other builders in town do exactly the same things. It's no secret now and it never has been. Everybody does zero down financing these days and down payment assistance. The lenders come up with this stuff not the builders.</td>
</tr>
