<hr />
I have a friend who is a realtor, and she thanks you for being smart enough to realize that parts of the process require some leg work.
<br />

<br />
She deals mostly with resort homes and stuff in Hide-A-Way Hills, but she printed your post and it lives in her little home office. She also has a copy she's giving to one of her new clients, because, in her opinion, they're dumb.
<br />

<br />
Loki and I have been working out our budgets just for apartments, and it's obvious based on our friends' reactions to our budgets that none of them have ever dealt with money on any scale larger than buying themselves new clothes. One of our friends was looking over our budget and flipped out because we could afford to rent a very nice townhome in Athens. He didn't take into account the utility bills, a food budget, or paying for gas to commute to class, as the townhomes are too far away to walk. Not to mention the renters' insurance. No wonder so many college students and young couples end up in financial trouble. I want my only debt out of college to be my damned student loans.</td>
